## Expected Result

| # | Expected Behaviour |
|---|---|
| 1 | Website sends a verification email to the provided address before granting any access |
| 2 | A message is displayed on screen: *"Please check your inbox to verify your email before continuing"* (or equivalent) |
| 3 | User is **not** granted any session, token, or access until the verification link in the email is clicked and confirmed |
| 4 | DevTools Network tab shows a call to a verification or magic-link endpoint (e.g. `/send-verification`, `/magic-link`), OR the identityToolkit response contains `"emailVerified": false` with **no** `idToken` returned |
| 5 | Navigating to `my-muse.ai/account` redirects the user back to the sign-in screen |
| 6 | Opening the Sign In modal should not trigger any server request before the user has entered any data |

---

## Actual Result

| # | Actual Behaviour |
|---|---|
| 1 | Opening the **"Sign In"** modal immediately triggered a pre-auth request to `httpapi` → `200 OK` (969 ms) — before any email was entered |
| 2 | No verification message was displayed on screen at any point after clicking Continue |
| 3 | User was immediately logged in and redirected — no additional confirmation step shown |
| 4 | `accounts:signInWithPassword` and `accounts:lookup` both returned `200 OK` — Firebase granted a full authenticated session instantly |
| 5 | **Payload tab** showed the email sent as a **URL query string parameter**, not in the request body |
| 6 | **Response tab** returned a full user profile in a single `200 OK` — including `user_id`, `email`, `geo`, `ip`, `created_at` and `updated_at` (identical timestamps), and `userFromFirestore: [{ "email": "musetest@gmail.com" }]` confirming the account was permanently written to the Firestore database with no pending or unverified state |
| 7 | `send_emails: true` was present in the response — the email system is configured but no verification email was dispatched |
| 8 | Network tab filtered by `verify` returned **0 / 36 requests** — no verification endpoint was called anywhere in the entire session |
| 9 | `my-muse.ai/account?email=musetest%40gmail.com` loaded successfully — **My Account** page displayed email and a live **Subscriptions** link with no redirect to sign-in |

---

## Root Cause Indicator

> Firebase Authentication is configured to create and activate accounts on first email submission with no verification gate. The server returns a full `idToken` and writes the user to Firestore in a single response. The application does not enforce `emailVerified: true` at any point before granting an authenticated session.

