## Additional Findings (Out of Scope — Separate TCs)

> The following issues were observed during this test session but are out of scope for WEB-TC-001. Noted here for triage — to be covered in separate test cases and bug reports.

| Finding | Notes |
|---|---|
| Email transmitted as URL query string parameter (`?email=musetest@gmail.com`) instead of POST body | Violates OWASP guidelines for PII handling — leaks in browser history, server logs, CDN logs |
| Pre-auth `httpapi` request fires on Sign In modal open before user enters any data | Investigate payload — may indicate premature session initialization |
| Internal config fields returned to client in auth response (`spam_project_id`, `sendios_config`, `capi_config`, `amplitude_config`) | Potential over-exposure of internal system configuration |

---

## Notes

- My Muse does not use passwords — email is the sole identifier. The absence of verification carries a higher risk than in a password-based system, as any actor can register using an email address they do not own.
- This test case covers **first-time sign-in (account creation) only**. Returning-user sign-in behaviour to be covered in a separate test case.
- This issue is cross-platform: the same vulnerability was observed on Android (see `Android BUG-003`). Neither platform enforces email verification.
- Bug filed as **WEB-BUG-001** with severity High.
